00:27:46.016 --> 00:27:46.806
you're going to place it.

00:27:46.806 --> 00:27:49.226
And, it lets you move objects to

00:27:49.226 --> 00:27:50.586
places that you can't see on the

00:27:50.586 --> 00:27:52.316
screen, by picking them up and

00:27:52.316 --> 00:27:52.716
turning.

00:27:52.716 --> 00:27:54.896
But, it still keeps that sense

00:27:54.896 --> 00:27:56.126
of physical interaction.

00:27:56.466 --> 00:27:57.266
That sense of direct

00:27:57.266 --> 00:27:59.666
manipulation that you had from

00:27:59.666 --> 00:28:01.166
picking up the object directly.

00:28:01.696 --> 00:28:04.006
So, if you support any kind of

00:28:04.006 --> 00:28:06.086
moving objects in AR in your

00:28:06.086 --> 00:28:07.916
apps, you should definitely

00:28:07.916 --> 00:28:09.786
support picking up an object

00:28:09.946 --> 00:28:11.526
with direct manipulation, and

00:28:11.526 --> 00:28:13.586
moving the device to find a new

00:28:13.586 --> 00:28:17.726
place to put it.

00:28:17.996 --> 00:28:20.686
Alright. So, moving your device

00:28:20.686 --> 00:28:22.016
and direct manipulation is one

00:28:22.016 --> 00:28:23.356
way to combine touch.

00:28:23.356 --> 00:28:25.766
But another way to combine touch

00:28:25.766 --> 00:28:27.386
with moving your device is

00:28:27.386 --> 00:28:28.826
through indirect controls.

00:28:29.006 --> 00:28:30.746
And, what I mean by indirect

00:28:30.746 --> 00:28:31.736
controls, are controls that are

00:28:31.736 --> 00:28:33.176
flat on the display.

00:28:33.856 --> 00:28:35.246
They're not placed in the world.

00:28:35.246 --> 00:28:36.006
They're not attached to

00:28:36.006 --> 00:28:36.526
anything.

00:28:36.866 --> 00:28:38.466
They're in a consistent position

00:28:38.466 --> 00:28:40.176
on the display, and you can

00:28:40.176 --> 00:28:41.176
learn that position.

00:28:41.496 --> 00:28:42.566
And, that's really great,

00:28:42.566 --> 00:28:43.576
because that means they get out

00:28:43.576 --> 00:28:44.156
of the way.

00:28:44.496 --> 00:28:45.256
Once you've learned that

00:28:45.256 --> 00:28:46.936
position of that control on the

00:28:46.936 --> 00:28:49.336
display, it stays in one place.

00:28:49.336 --> 00:28:50.586
You can rest your finger above

00:28:50.586 --> 00:28:51.986
it while you're speeding your

00:28:51.986 --> 00:28:54.036
time focusing on the rest of the

00:28:54.036 --> 00:28:54.326
app.

00:28:54.326 --> 00:28:56.846
